  "text": "Our analysis shows that the assumption of the power (or CRRA) form for the felicity function is inconsistent with well documented features of the micro-data on intra-temporal allocation. Our analysis supports the results of [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] who find evidence that the EIS is not constant. Our paper provides a further explanation for those results: the EIS cannot be constant because the within period allocations of rich and poor households differ in a complicated way.",
